==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coyness
<hw>Coy"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of being coy; feigned
o<?/ bashful unwillingness to become familiar; reserve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the kind nymph would <qex>coyness</qex> feign,⟦br⟧
And hides but to be found again.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Reserve; shrinking; shyness; backwardness;
modesty; bashfulness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>coyol</ent>⟦br⟧
